[
    {
        "content": "<p>I'd like to redefine <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/ring.inverse\">docs#ring.inverse</a> for a <a href=\"https://leanprover-community.github.io/mathlib_docs/find/monoid_with_zero\">docs#monoid_with_zero</a> instead of a ring (why not?). Probably this means that it should be renamed. What name would you suggest? <code>inverse₀</code>? Something better?</p>",
        "id": 212264567,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1601881230
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"260507\">@Heather Macbeth</span> <span class=\"user-mention\" data-user-id=\"112680\">@Johan Commelin</span></p>",
        "id": 212264578,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1601881247
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do you even need the zero?</p>",
        "id": 212264617,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1601881313
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Can't you just do this for any monoid?</p>",
        "id": 212264644,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1601881323
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>It's zero for non-invertible elements.</p>",
        "id": 212265057,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1601881777
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I can redefine it to be <code>1</code> in this case. Then it won't agree with <code>has_inv.inv</code> for fields but this should not be too important.</p>",
        "id": 212265138,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1601881861
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Yeah... I can understand that <code>0</code> might be convenient</p>",
        "id": 212265324,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1601882078
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I would abbreviate it to <code>inv\\0</code> if you choose the <code>monoid_with_zero</code> route</p>",
        "id": 212265340,
        "sender_full_name": "Johan Commelin",
        "timestamp": 1601882105
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>No objections.  I like <code>inverse₀</code> or <code>inv₀</code>.  Do you have a use in mind?</p>",
        "id": 212291456,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1601900685
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Note that it will probably conflict with <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/issues/4407\">#4407</a>.</p>",
        "id": 212291552,
        "sender_full_name": "Heather Macbeth",
        "timestamp": 1601900740
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I just wanted to apply results about <code>ring.inverse</code> to the usual division, and noticed that the definition doesn't use addition.</p>",
        "id": 212298198,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1601904307
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Do we still want to rename this? The generalization was made without a rename in <a href=\"https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib/issues/6603\">#6603</a></p>",
        "id": 259036394,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1635206754
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I don't care about the name.</p>",
        "id": 259058017,
        "sender_full_name": "Yury G. Kudryashov",
        "timestamp": 1635231281
    }
